    "description": "Tata Memorial Centre, one of India's leading organizations, is hiring a Surgeon for our Srinagar operations. We offer a competitive salary package along with world-class benefits.\n\nAbout Tata Memorial Centre:\nTata Memorial Centre is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBBS / MD / MS from recognized medical college\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Flexible working hours\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Srinagar, Jammu & Kashmir, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Tata Memorial Centre!",
